column5: Heading out to Lake Joe for lakers Saturday if the weather will co-operate for me. Anyone been out lately, what depths are working for ya?? Other advice appreciated??
Lake Joe in Muskoka?  I fish Rosseau, and 50-60 feet has been good for me.
Sorry Ya Muskoka Lake Joe!  Thanks for the info I will try that depth first
Thats a good lake there that lake Joe.At least that name is a good name there that name Joe. Joe

.. yes Joe is a heckuva good lake ... havent really fished lakers there this time of year but have had alot of success there in the hardwater season ... alot .... and some BIGUNS ... 25+lbs to be had ... my guess would be deep (50 +) and slow ...  Let us know how you do !
